  "doc_id": "6660",
  "text": "Isolates were cultivated overnight in tryptic soy broth (Difco) with 0.5% glucose at 37°C with 5% CO 2 , and biofilm was determined using crystal violet as described by Holmberg [CITATION_1] with modifications as described previously [CITATION_2] . The experiment was repeated 3 times. Medium alone was used as negative control. The negative control absorbance values were subtracted from the isolates' absorbance values in each experiment. A strain of Enterococcus faecalis, known to be a potent biofilm producer, was used for positive control. Heparinized plasma was obtained by centrifugation of blood from a healthy donor at 1500 g for 10 minutes.",
